{"lemma":"غالِيَةٌ","slug":"غالِيَةٌ","root":"غ.ل.#","root_slug":"غ-ل-_","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ل-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32332","n32342"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Gallic, Gaulish"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Gaul (native or inhabitant of the historical region of Gaul, or poetically the modern nation of France) (usually male)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"غَال (ḡāl, “Gauls”) + ـِيّ (-iyy)."},"ipa":["/ɣaː.liː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32332","headword_ar":"غَالِيَةٌ","root":"glw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"glY","text_ar":"غلى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n32342","headword_ar":"غَالِيَةٌ","root":"glY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Galia moschata,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of perfume,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain compound of perfumes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"musk mixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boiled"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with other perfumes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (MA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a perfume composed of musk and ambergris and camphor and oil of ben:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:) it is said that the first who called it thus was Suleymán Ibn-'Abd-El-Melik; (S, TA;) and he did so because it is a compound boiled together upon the fire: or it was thus named by Mo'áwiyeh; the case being, that 'Abd-Allah Ibn-Jaafar went in to him, and the odour of perfume was diffusing itself from him; so he said, “ What is thy perfume, O 'Abd-Allah? ” and he answered, “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"musk and ambergris combined with oil of ben;"},{"kind":"text","text":"” whereupon Mo'áwiyeh said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAliyapN","text_ar":"غَالِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highpriced:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [hence some hold the word to belong to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"glw","text_ar":"غلو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and their opinion is strengthened by the fact that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galowaY","text_ar":"غَلْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"glw","text_ar":"غلو"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","KL","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}